race.comment: TEQUILA BABY (3) progressive mare with a fitness edge over the bulk of these fifth-up. Set a career peak with the 58kg when pulling out plenty to get the job done over 1200m at Warwick Farm. Braith Nock sticks, and she ticks all the boxes again. CRYPTONIC (2) chasing her third-straight victory after returning with a fast-finishing win over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Strengthened over the break and can go on with it now. LET'S GO AGAIN (9) covered a stack of ground at her third run back from the wide gate when a fighting fifth over 1100m at Randwick. Looks the value play from the barrier. ART VOLANT (1) smart when right and back in class third-up. Tongue-tie goes on and will appreciate Roper's 2kg claim from the sticky draw. Improved showing anticipated. ZOUTASTIC (5) three weeks between runs when she knocked up to run fourth over this trip at Gosford. One for the exotics.
